-- Lebanon's Byblos Bank Posts 15% Increase in First-Half Profit on Deposits
-- Massoud A. Derhally
-- 2010-07-30T09:46:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/lebanon-s-byblos-bank-posts-15-increase-in-first-half-profit-on-deposits.html

          
          
             Byblos Bank SAL , the third largest
Lebanese lender by assets, posted a 15 percent rise in first-
half profit on increased driven by growth in both net interest
income and net commission income.  
 Profit advanced to $72.4 million in the first six months of
the year, from $63 million for the same period a year earlier,
the bank said in an e-mailed statement today.  
 Loans advanced 8.9 percent to $3.48 billion and customer
deposits increased 8.8 percent to $11.2 billion at the end of
June. Total assets increased by 7.6 percent during the first
half of the year to $14.6 billion, the bank said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Massoud A. Derhally  in Beirut, Lebanon at   mderhally@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        